Fuzzy Search
----field----
field: {E4671EDD-3EB2-4634-A944-B5D86397D111}
name: Tip Text
key: tip text
content-length: 907

For searches you can place a fuzzy search on it with the following syntax %
When you enter the % character, a slider will show up for you to weight the importance or priority of a search filter.
For example, text:Sample% will prompt a slider. If you place 80% it will then ask you to fill in the text. This will now tell the search that if there are other search parameters for text that aren't using a fuzzy search then the results will prioritise that other search term will ordering the results. 
To give a guide, you will notice the text get blurrier the more "fuzzy" the search.
The syntax is air~0-1 e.g. air~0.8&nbsp;
The close the number is to one, the more particular the filter will be e.g. a number close to 0 will be more and more fuzzy and bring back results that are not as much of a match as if you had a higher number. The default is 0.5.
This search can also be used for sounds like search.
